                                        <h2>Australia MLTSSL List</h2><br>

                                        <div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element  custom_1553585446556">
                                            <div class="wpb_wrapper">
                                                <p>There are 212 occupations in the Medium and Long-Term Strategic
                                                    Skills List (MLTSSL). This list is prescribed in the Occupations
                                                    Specification and Evaluation Authorities legislative instrument LIN
                                                    19/051. In order to selected for&nbsp; the skilled migration to
                                                    Australia (Subclass 189), you must select an occupation from the
                                                    Medium and Long-term Strategic Skills List (MLTSSL).</p>

                                                <p>When you apply for a General Skilled Migration Visa and you are NOT
                                                    nominated by a government of the State or Territory, you must
                                                    nominate an occupation from this List of Medium and Long-term
                                                    Strategic Skills.Because Australia is desperately in need of filling
                                                    the labor gap with highly skilled and skilled workers to develop its
                                                    economy. The new list started on April 19, 2018. A candidate should
                                                    ensure that the nominated occupation in which he / she is intended
                                                    to apply is listed on MLTSSL or not before applying for Australia
                                                    Permanent Residency.,</p>

                                                <br> <h4 style="text-align: left" class="custom_heading"><strong>The
                                                        Listapplies to applicants who:</strong></h4><br>

                                                <div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element custom_1570255449293">
                                                    <div class="wpb_wrapper">
                                                        <p>1. Are issued an invitation on or after 11 March 2019 to make
                                                            an application for a&nbsp;<strong>Subclass 189</strong>&nbsp;(Skilled
                                                            Independent) visa</p>

                                                        <p>2. Are issued an invitation on or after 11 March 2019 to make
                                                            an application for a&nbsp;<strong>Subclass 489</strong>&nbsp;(Skilled
                                                            Regional (Provisional) (NOT nominated by a State or
                                                            Territory government agency) visa</p>

                                                        <p>3. Apply on or after 11 March 2019 for a&nbsp;<strong>Subclass
                                                                485</strong>&nbsp;(Temporary Graduate) visa</p>

                                                        <p>4. Are nominated by a State or Territory government agency
                                                            and are issued an invitation on or after 11 March 2019 to
                                                            make an application for a&nbsp;<strong>Subclass 190</strong>&nbsp;(Skilled
                                                            nominated) visa or&nbsp;<strong>Subclass 489</strong>&nbsp;(Skilled
                                                            Regional (Provisional) (State or Territory government agency
                                                            nominated)) visa</p>

                                                        <br>

                                                        <h2>Australia STSOL List 2020</h2><br>

                                                        <p>STSOL stands for Short-Term Skilled Occupational List. The
                                                            Australian Skilled Occupancy List (STSOL) is used as part of
                                                            the Australian immigration point system. You must select an
                                                            occupation from the Short-Term Skilled Occupation List
                                                            (STSOL) if you apply for eligible migration through the
                                                            nomination of a State or Territory Government.</p>

                                                        <p>There are 215 occupations in the Short-Term Skilled
                                                            Occupation List (STSOL). This list is prescribed in
                                                            legislative instrument LIN 19/051: Specification of
                                                            Occupations and Assessing Authorities.</p>

                                                        <br>

                                                        <h2>Innovation and Investment Visa</h2><br>

                                                        <p>How do you define success? Corner office, lots of money,
                                                            working at a job you enjoy so much it doesnâ€™t seem like a
                                                            job? There are thousands of ways to describe what success
                                                            is. Success can come in any size, but when you are looking
                                                            to succeed on a greater scale, advice from the people at the
                                                            top of their game is the most relevant. Business Review
                                                            Australia has compiled definitions for divergent success. A
                                                            breathtaking landscape in collaboration with myriad range of
                                                            opportunities is something that is quintessentially
                                                            Australia.</p>

                                                        <p>The Business Innovation and Investment (Permanent) visa
                                                            (subclass 888) can be applied after the fulfilment of the
                                                            criteria of the Business Innovation and Investment
                                                            (Provisional) visa (subclass 188) and hence is the second
                                                            stage of visa acquirement. The new Expression of Interest
                                                            (EOI) needs to be submitted or invitation letter for visa
                                                            application. If you are seeking for the initial level
                                                            fulfillment you should be nominated by a State or Territory
                                                            government agency or Austrade on behalf of the Australian
                                                            government. If you hold Provisional Business Innovation and
                                                            Investment visa (subclass 188) you must have authentic proof
                                                            to demonstrate that the government entity has not withdrawn
                                                            the nomination by any chance, which had nominated you for
                                                            same visa.</p>

                                                        <p>There are two main streams on the basis of which the
                                                            provisional visa is applied:</p>
                                                        <ul>
                                                            <li><b>Business Innovation Stream:</b>&nbsp;It requests to
                                                                have a settled business in Australia which fulfils some
                                                                fixed turnover conditions.
                                                            </li>
                                                            <li><b>Investor Stream:</b>&nbsp;Have a grasped investment
                                                                in Australia circumscription for 4 years
                                                            </li>
                                                        </ul>
                                                        <br>

                                                        <h2 class="western"><strong>Business Innovation stream</strong>
                                                        </h2><br>
                                                        <ul>
                                                            <li>For application of the Business Innovation
                                                                stream, you must have been in Australia and acquired the
                                                                following:
                                                            </li>
                                                            <li>a Business Innovation and Investment (Provisional) visa
                                                                (subclass 188) in the Business Innovation stream or the
                                                                Business Innovation Extension stream
                                                            </li>
                                                            <li>a Special Category visa (subclass 444)</li>
                                                            <li>For minimum one year in the two years immediately before
                                                                you apply for the visa.
                                                            </li>
                                                            <li>Also, you must be able to demonstrate proof of
                                                                involvement in a current business satisfying the
                                                                financial conditions and have offered employments to
                                                                Australian citizens.
                                                            </li>
                                                        </ul>

